<h1>version 1: static ideas and simple contexts</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>

You already have tons of things you know you want, can, or should do. 
I am not here to suggest curated content for your consumption. 
Instead take simple contexts of time, day, location
and what I know about myself to make suggestions of what do do now.

<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
  <li>preset non-personalized suggestions</li>
  <li>suggestions are weighted by various contexts</li>
</ul>

<h2>Backend</h2>

<h3>transmission</h3>

<strong>xhr post with time/location</strong>
<pre>
  {time: 15, location: 'home'}
</pre>

<strong>return array of hashes</strong>
<pre>
  [
    {time: 15, idea: 'read magazine article', weight: 10},
    {time: 15, idea: 'call mom', weight: 5},
    {time: 15, idea: 'make dinner plans', weight: 1}
  ]
</pre>

<h3>logic</h3>

<strong>apply context multipliers</strong>
<pre>
  weight(idea A) = 
    (current day X contexts(idea a)[day]) X (current time X contexts(idea a)[time]) X (...other contexts...)

  contexts(idea A) = 
    {
      time:     {morning: 1, noon: 1, afternoon: 2, evening: 1, night: 0},
      day:      {monday-friday: 1, saturday-sunday: 2},
      location: {home: 1, work: 0}
    }
</pre>

<h3>models</h3>

<strong>ideas</strong>
holds ideas like 'read a book, 'call a friend'

<pre>
  id:         integer
  name:       string
  created_at: date
  updated_at: date
</pre>

<strong>contexts</strong>
holds contexts like 'location', 'time', 'day'

<pre>
  id:   integer
  name: string
</pre>

<strong>contexts_options</strong>
holds options of a context like 'morning', 'afternoon', 'night'

<pre>
  id:         integer
  context_id: integer
  name:       string
</pre>

<strong>idea_weights</strong>
holds weights for an option like 'morning' for a context like 'time' for an idea like 'read a book'

<pre>
  id:                 integer
  idea_id:            integer
  context_id:         integer
  context_option_id:  integer
  weight:             integer
</pre>

