<h1>version 1.5: record feedback and get more ideas</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>
  version 1 is good, but the universe of ideas is small and I quickly cycle 
  through the suggestions. I'd like to be able to suggest ideas for myself and 
  the community.
</p>

<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Accounts ('Users') allows us to keep track of feedback and other UGC</li>
  <li>Users can add suggest ideas and contexts for them</li>
</ul>

<h2>Backend</h2>

<h3>models</h3>

<strong>ideas</strong> is expanded to hold a created_by field

<pre>
  created_by: integer
</pre>

<strong>users</strong> holds user accounts

<pre>
  id:     integer
  email:  string
  admin:  boolean, false
  ... devise fields
</pre>


<h1>version 2.0: dynamic ideas and feedback</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>version 1.5 is good, but I often cycle through things I can't do or 
don't want to do in order to find good ideas. For example, there is 
no point in suggesting that I call my mother when I'm at work just 
because I have fifteen minutes if she is working right now or lives 
across the world and is sleeping.</p>

<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Skip suggestions are recorded, with reasons as per rejection</li>
  <li>Personalization context</li>
</ul>

<h3>allow content to be added "suggested" (user generated)</h3>

* ask for gender

* record passovers (I don't want to do this at all vs. I don't want to do this right now)
  - new context multipliers to consider
    idea A X personal_multiplier X community_multiplier

* connect to calendar (supplement how much time do you have)
* set workplace location
* set work schedule (9-5)
* set home location
* suggest content via connected sources (instapaper)